'''TRIzol'''，是一種能分離RNA、DNA、蛋白質的試劑。該試劑常溫下爲紫紅色液體。其主要成分爲[[苯酚|苯酚]]和[[硫氰化胍|硫氰化胍]]。苯酚具有毒性和腐蝕性，而硫氰化胍則具有刺激性<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cellbiology.med.unsw.edu.au/units/lab/msds/Trizol.pdf |title=Material Safety data sheet from Life technologies. |accessdate=2016-01-28 |archive-date=2008-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080721185232/http://cellbiology.med.unsw.edu.au/units/lab/msds/Trizol.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mrcgene.com/msdsrna.htm |title=Material Safety data sheet from MRC |accessdate=2016-01-28 |archive-date=2008-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081228194341/http://mrcgene.com/msdsrna.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。該試劑是以Piotr Chomczyński與Sacchi, N在1987年提出的一步分離RNA法爲基礎發明的<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2440339 |title=Chomczynski P, Sacchi N. Single-step method of RNA isolation by acid guanidinium thiocyanate-phenol-chloroform extraction. Anal Biochem. 1987 Apr;162(1):156-9. |accessdate=2016-01-28 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305213055/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2440339 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

TRIzol爲由{{Link-en|生命科技 (熱爾科技)|Life Technologies (Thermo Fisher Scientific)|生命科技}}（Life Technologies）持有的商標，而由MRC生產的同種試劑則名爲TRI Reagent（Reagent，意爲「試劑」）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mrcgene.com/rna-isolation/tri-reagent-rt|title=TRI Reagent® RT / TRI Reagent® RT-Liquid Samples|publisher=MRC|accessdate=2016-01-28|archive-date=2016-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220001634/http://mrcgene.com/rna-isolation/tri-reagent-rt|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==用法簡述==
將組織或培養的細胞與TRIzol混合後，經一定處理，再加入[[氯仿|氯仿]]並離心，即可得分爲三層的液體。無色透明的上層水層、中間層、以及紫紅色的下層有機層。其中，RNA位於上層，DNA位於中間層和下層，蛋白質位於下層。之後，即可先後分離出RNA、DNA和蛋白質<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tools.thermofisher.com/content/sfs/manuals/trizol_reagent.pdf|title=Instruction of TRIzol Reagent|publisher=Thermo Fisher Scientific|accessdate=2016-01-28|archive-date=2016-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204121623/https://tools.thermofisher.com/content/sfs/manuals/trizol_reagent.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

